0:09:51.720,0:09:56.360
We found it very comfortable to neglect the existence of God.

0:09:56.360,0:10:02.160
Because there was someone castigating the man of God, we could say, "There was no God".

0:10:02.160,0:10:06.040
Our conclusion was that all of them were the same.

0:10:06.040,0:10:08.840
I asked him, if he wanted to escape paying my money.

0:10:08.840,0:10:14.800
I wanted to treat myself, I had spent all my money; I sold my car...

0:10:14.800,0:10:20.300
He told me of somebody who had diabetes, who had come and had received the Morning Water;

0:10:20.300,0:10:22.640
he was healed before he got home.

0:10:22.640,0:10:24.760
I told him to stop all those stories .

0:10:24.760,0:10:28.960
Then a friend of mine, who resides in Bayelsa State, was burying his mother;

0:10:28.960,0:10:30.720
I went to his mothers burial.

0:10:30.720,0:10:34.380
I then opened up to him, telling him what I was going through.

0:10:34.380,0:10:35.880
He is a member of this church.

0:10:35.880,0:10:37.680
He asked me If I had gone to The SCOAN.

0:10:37.680,0:10:39.520
I asked him to leave that conversation.

0:10:39.520,0:10:41.080
He tried preaching to me.

0:10:41.080,0:10:45.780
While the hearse was still going, he told me that I needed to go to The SCOAN.

0:10:45.780,0:10:49.720
I said I didn't want to go there, but he insisted.

0:10:49.720,0:10:54.220
At that time he provoked me and said, "Young man, if you choose to want to know God; - know God.

0:10:54.220,0:11:02.340
If you choose not to want to know God - leave it. This life is a battlefield and not a playground."

0:11:02.340,0:11:06.980
After he had said this I was contemplating, "This word is a battlefield and not a playground.

0:11:06.980,0:11:11.200
If you choose to want to know God - know God 
if you don't want - leave it"

0:11:11.200,0:11:14.380
At that time, these words kept ringing inside my mind.

0:11:14.380,0:11:16.760
When I tried to forget about it, it didn't go away easily.

0:11:16.760,0:11:20.280
It became as a little stream in my heart that refused to get dry.

0:11:20.280,0:11:22.140
At that time, there was a hotel I used to stay in.

0:11:22.140,0:11:27.580
At that time, I didn't go out "openly"; I always went to the rural areas and lodged there,

0:11:27.580,0:11:31.160
